---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="Our Priorities | Tim Dorr for Georgia"
  description="Explore Tim Dorr's priorities for Georgia, including education, a sustainable economy, and accessible healthcare. Real solutions for House District 53."
>
  <main class="space-y-16 bg-slate-50 py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl space-y-24 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-4 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-black tracking-tight text-balance uppercase sm:text-6xl">Our Priorities</h1>
        <div class="bg-brand-orange mx-auto h-2 w-20 rounded-full"></div>
        <p class="text-xl font-medium text-slate-600">
          Real solutions for the real problems facing Georgia House District 53.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-16">
        <!-- Education Section -->
        <section
          class="flex flex-col gap-12 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm sm:p-12 lg:flex-row"
        >
          <div class="flex-1 space-y-6">
            <div
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-blue-200 bg-blue-100 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-bold tracking-widest text-blue-700 uppercase"
            >
              Education
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 uppercase">Strong schools, strong future</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none space-y-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
              <p>As a parent, this one hits close to home.</p>
              <p>We all want our kids to have opportunities. We want them to learn, to grow, and to be prepared for whatever comes next.</p>
              <p>But too often, families feel like they're navigating a system that is stretched thin. Teachers are doing more with less, parents are stepping in to fill gaps, and students are not always getting the support they need.</p>
              <p>We can do better.</p>
              <p>We need to invest in our public schools, support our teachers, and make sure every child, no matter their zip code, has access to a high-quality education.</p>
              <p>Because when our schools are strong, our communities are stronger.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex aspect-video flex-1 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 text-slate-400"
          >
            [Classroom/School Photo]
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Economy Section -->
        <section
          class="flex flex-col gap-12 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm sm:p-12 lg:flex-row-reverse"
        >
          <div class="flex-1 space-y-6">
            <div
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-green-200 bg-green-100 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-bold tracking-widest text-green-700 uppercase"
            >
              Economy
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-balance text-slate-900 uppercase">Making life more affordable and building a stronger future</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none space-y-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
              <p>Right now, families are feeling the pressure.</p>
              <p>Everyday costs keep rising, and for many, it feels like no matter how hard you work, it is getting harder to get ahead.</p>
              <p>A strong economy should work for everyone, not just a few.</p>
              <p>We need smarter, more efficient approaches that help lower costs today while building a more sustainable and competitive future for Georgia.</p>
              <p>That means supporting job growth, encouraging innovation, and investing in solutions that save families money while strengthening our economy.</p>
              <p>Because progress should make life easier, not more expensive.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex aspect-video flex-1 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 text-slate-400"
          >
            [Local Main Street Photo]
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Healthcare Section -->
        <section
          class="flex flex-col gap-12 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 text-balance shadow-sm sm:p-12 lg:flex-row"
        >
          <div class="flex-1 space-y-6">
            <div
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-red-200 bg-red-100 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-bold tracking-widest text-red-700 uppercase"
            >
              Healthcare
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 uppercase">No one should delay care because of cost</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none space-y-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
              <p>I have seen families put off doctor visits, not because they do not care about their health, but because they are worried about the bill.</p>
              <p>That is a tough position to be in. No one should have to choose between taking care of themselves and taking care of their finances.</p>
              <p>Healthcare should be accessible, affordable, and focused on people, not paperwork.</p>
              <p>We need to expand access, reduce costs, and support providers so families can get the care they need when they need it.</p>
              <p>Because peace of mind should not come with a price tag.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex aspect-video flex-1 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 text-slate-400"
          >
            [Local Clinic/Hospital Photo]
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Housing Section -->
        <section
          class="flex flex-col gap-12 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm sm:p-12 lg:flex-row-reverse"
        >
          <div class="flex-1 space-y-6">
            <div
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-purple-200 bg-purple-100 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-bold tracking-widest text-purple-700 uppercase"
            >
              Housing
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-balance text-slate-900 uppercase">Making it easier to live where you work</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none space-y-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
              <p>One of the biggest stresses for families today is not just making a living, it is affording a place to live.</p>
              <p>I have talked to people who want to stay in the communities they love, close to their jobs, their schools, and their support systems, but feel like they are being priced out. I have seen young families delay buying a home, and longtime residents worry about whether they can keep the one they have.</p>
              <p>That is not sustainable.</p>
              <p>Housing is not just about buildings. It is about stability. It is about being able to put down roots, raise a family, and feel like you belong.</p>
              <p>We need practical solutions that increase housing availability, support responsible development, and protect the character of our communities so people are not forced to choose between affordability and quality of life.</p>
              <p>Because where you live should not feel like a constant source of stress.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex aspect-video flex-1 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 text-slate-400"
          >
            [Housing Photo]
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Childcare & Working Families Section -->
        <section
          class="flex flex-col gap-12 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm sm:p-12 lg:flex-row"
        >
          <div class="flex-1 space-y-6">
            <div
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-orange-200 bg-orange-100 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-bold tracking-widest text-orange-700 uppercase"
            >
              Childcare & Working Families
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 uppercase">Supporting the people holding everything together</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none space-y-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
              <p>I have talked to parents who are working full-time and still trying to figure out how to cover childcare.</p>
              <p>It is one of the biggest pressures families face, and it affects everything from careers to finances to the ability to plan for the future.</p>
              <p>For many families, it is not just expensive. It is overwhelming.</p>
              <p>We need solutions that make childcare more affordable and more accessible while supporting working families who are balancing a lot every single day.</p>
              <p>Because the people holding everything together should not feel like they are barely holding on.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="flex aspect-video flex-1 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 text-slate-400"
          >
            [Childcare Photo]
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
